DESCRIPTION
The runbook says every tier needs unanimous reviewer pass and reviewer failures escalate, but recent captured work proceeded when pilms was unavailable or a reviewer malfunction was ground-truth-disproven. Make this policy explicit instead of relying on ad-hoc exceptions.

Acceptance:
- define when a reviewer outage, empty output, auth/quota failure, or tool malfunction blocks the gate
- define when a reviewer seat can be disregarded after ground-truth verification, and what evidence is required
- define whether a degraded 3-seat gate is ever allowed, who can authorize it, and how it is recorded
- update review-gate-runbook.md and review-gate-process.md consistently
- ensure degraded mode is compatible with the upcoming gate reviewer visibility schema

