**Files:**
- docs/plans/dogfood/review-gate-runbook.md — Add a new top-level "## Degraded
  Gate Policy" section (placed right after "Result Classification", since that is
  where the fallback paragraph lives today). It CONSOLIDATES, not duplicates:
  state the default strict rule, then the FOUR explicit sub-rules and
  cross-reference the existing prose rather than re-spelling it.
  (1) BLOCKS-the-gate vs recoverable-retry: a seat that exits with
  auth/quota/model-access/timeout/tool-invocation failure, OR returns empty/no
  verdict, is FIRST a recoverable retry — reroll and root-cause per "Waiting And
  Status" (the 2nd-occurrence debug rule, the pi/pilms reasoning budget, the
  0-CPU-hang diagnosis). It BLOCKS the gate (incomplete, escalate) UNTIL it is
  either resolved or meets the bounded-exception bar below; an unresolved/
  undiagnosed failure is never a GO (verdict `failed`/`empty`, gate incomplete).
  (2) DISREGARD a seat: ONLY a SINGLE seat with a REPRODUCIBLE TOOLING outage
  (empty/hang/auth/quota, recurring after >=2 rerolls, root-caused to a KNOWN
  tooling artifact — e.g. pilms 0-CPU hang, codex go-test hang, pilms empty
  completion — NOT substantive dissent) MAY be disregarded WHEN the other THREE
  seats are unanimous substantive GO after thorough review. Required EVIDENCE:
  which seat, the artifact/diagnosis, and reroll evidence. REROLL BAR: >=2 rerolls
  to ESTABLISH a NOVEL tooling outage as reproducible + root-caused; for an outage
  ALREADY documented in this runbook as a known root-caused artifact (e.g. the
  pi/pilms 0-CPU client hang under "Third failure mode"), the documented single
  confirming reroll suffices. This shortcut is BOUNDED to already-known,
  already-root-caused artifacts — it is NOT a general 1-reroll allowance, and a
  novel/undiagnosed outage always needs >=2. A DISPROVEN BLOCK (ground-truth contradicts a factual claim)
  is NOT disregarding — cross-reference the existing disputed-factual-claim rule:
  verify empirically, do NOT apply the change, rerun with evidence embedded. A
  substantive BLOCK is never disregarded.
  (3) Degraded 3-seat gate allowed? YES, bounded to rule (2). WHO authorizes: in
  an autonomous /loop there is no real-time user, so the ORCHESTRATOR authorizes
  under these explicit conditions and records it; OUTSIDE an autonomous loop,
  escalate to the user. HOW recorded (cross-ref Recording Results + the verdict
  mapping table): the outage seat carries verdict `malfunction` (or `empty`) with
  a `failure_note`, the degraded pass carries seat verdict `disregarded` +
  `failure_note` AND `decision.degraded_reason` (which seat, evidence, reroll
  count), the gate is a recorded `GateAttempt` (status `pass`), and the prose
  mirror notes the outage.
  (4) Schema mapping (cross-ref gate-reviewer-record-schema.md / docs/gates.md):
  outage -> `failed`/`empty`/`malfunction`; disregarded seat -> `disregarded` +
  `failure_note` + `decision.degraded_reason`; degraded pass is a normal recorded
  `GateAttempt`. State this so degraded gates are captured STRUCTURALLY, not just
  in prose.
  Then RENAME/cross-link the existing "Autonomous-loop tooling-outage fallback"
